section.def:
constitution
                (章程) means the articles of constitution referred
            to in section 4 and specified in the Schedule;

corporation
                (法團) means the Matilda and War Memorial Hospital
            named and incorporated in accordance with the provisions of section 3;

Ordinance (條例)
                means the Matilda and War Memorial Hospital Ordinance (Cap.
                    1035);

subparagraph.content:
to provide facilities for training in medicine, surgery, dentistry,
                        nursing and hospital work and all kinds of medical, surgical, nursing and
                        dental care;

paragraph.content:
to determine who shall be entitled to sign on the corporation’s behalf
                    bills, notes, receipts, acceptances, endorsements, cheques, releases, contracts
                    and documents;

one member who and whose successors shall be appointed by the Chairman and
                    Senior Managing Director for the time being of Jardine, Matheson & Co.,
                    Limited;

one member who and whose successors shall be appointed by the senior
                    resident executive for the time being in Hong Kong of the Swire Group of
                    Companies;
